author: John Kennedy
title: Florida Senate sniping in special session on redistricting
text:
Republican senators continued sniping Wednesday while reviewing plans for redrawing their election boundaries and a seat numbering scheme that could help a leadership bid by Joe Negron , a Palm Beach County lawmaker at least for now.
Senate Redistricting Chairman Bill Galvano advanced the position that only half the 40-member Senate should face re-election next year – even if virtually every district is changed in the effort to comply with a legal settlement with voters’ groups.
